{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778991185709,"sessionID":"ses_1cbe49a24ffeMllnW9kPHlNnLD","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_3XVPpzM68x7e2Qedfbd6NFkj","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_1990334.obo\n@@\n id: GO:1990334\n-name: Bfa1-Bub2 complex\n+name: SIN/MEN two-component GAP complex\n namespace: cellular_component\n-def: \"A protein complex that acts as a two-component GTPase-activating protein for Tem1 GTPase, thus regulating a signal transduction cascade, called the mitotic exit network (MEN), which is required for mitotic exit and cytokinesis. Bub2/Bfa1 keeps Tem1 inactive until the spindle is properly oriented, thus inhibiting MEN activation.\" [GOC:bhm, PMID:16449187]\n+def: \"A protein complex that acts as a two-component GTPase-activating protein in the septation initiation network (SIN) or mitotic exit network (MEN), thereby helping regulate signaling required for mitotic exit and cytokinesis. In budding yeast, the Bub2-Bfa1 complex keeps Tem1 inactive until the spindle is properly oriented, thus inhibiting MEN activation.\" [PMID:16449187, PMID:22525225]\n+synonym: \"Bfa1-Bub2 complex\" NARROW []\n+synonym: \"Byr4-Cdc16 GAP complex\" NARROW []\n is_a: GO:1902773 ! GTPase activator complex\n relationship: part_of GO:0005816 ! spindle pole body\n+property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31636\" xsd:anyURI\n created_by: bhm\n creation_date: 2014-03-17T14:34:21Z\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+## Issue #31636: GO:1990334 rename\n+\n+- No dedicated DOSDP appears necessary for this edit.\n+- This is an existing cellular component protein complex term with no logical definition.\n+- Precedent in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo` supports species-agnostic umbrella labels for conserved SIN/MEN complexes, especially `GO:0160065` `SIN/MEN signaling complex`.\n+- For this issue, the design choice is:\n+  - keep the existing asserted parent and relationships unchanged\n+  - avoid adding `intersection_of` axioms\n+  - use a broader, pan-species label for the main term\n+  - retain species-specific legacy names as `NARROW` synonyms\n+\n+Relevant precedent:\n+\n+- `GO:0160065` `SIN/MEN signaling complex`\n+- `GO:1990811` `MWP complex` with founding-species synonym retained as `EXACT`\n+- `GO:1990879` `CST complex` with species-specific complexes retained as `NARROW`\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+## PMID:16449187 \"Disappearance of the budding yeast Bub2-Bfa1 complex from the mother-bound spindle pole contributes to mitotic exit\"\n+\n+Primary experimental support for the existing Saccharomyces example. Confirms that Bub2 and Bfa1 function together as a two-component GAP regulating Tem1 and mitotic exit.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:16449187 \"Budding yeast spindle position checkpoint is engaged by misoriented spindles and prevents mitotic exit by inhibiting the G protein Tem1 through the GTPase-activating protein (GAP) Bub2/Bfa1.\"\n+    - Bub2/Bfa1 is explicitly described as the GAP acting on Tem1.\n+    - This supports retaining the budding-yeast complex name as a narrow synonym and as the organism-specific example in the definition.\n+\n+## PMID:22525225 \"Hippo signalling in the G2/M cell cycle phase: lessons learned from the yeast MEN and SIN pathways\"\n+\n+Review-level support that MEN in budding yeast and SIN in fission yeast are cognate signaling systems, justifying a species-agnostic umbrella label spanning both networks.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:22525225 \"All members of the Hippo core signalling cassette are conserved from yeast to humans, whereby the yeast analogues of Hippo, Mats and Lats are central components of the mitotic exit network and septation initiation network in budding and fission yeast, respectively.\"\n+    - Supports treating MEN and SIN as corresponding conserved yeast signaling systems.\n+    - Justifies broadening the primary term label from the budding-yeast-specific `Bfa1-Bub2 complex` to `SIN/MEN two-component GAP complex`.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nM terms/GO_1990334.obo\nA DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\nA RESEARCH.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_1990334.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_1990334.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_1990334.obo\n@@ -1,10 +1,12 @@\n [Term]\n id: GO:1990334\n-name: Bfa1-Bub2 complex\n+name: SIN/MEN two-component GAP complex\n namespace: cellular_component\n-def: \"A protein complex that acts as a two-component GTPase-activating protein for Tem1 GTPase, thus regulating a signal transduction cascade, called the mitotic exit network (MEN), which is required for mitotic exit and cytokinesis. Bub2/Bfa1 keeps Tem1 inactive until the spindle is properly oriented, thus inhibiting MEN activation.\" [GOC:bhm, PMID:16449187]\n+def: \"A protein complex that acts as a two-component GTPase-activating protein in the septation initiation network (SIN) or mitotic exit network (MEN), thereby helping regulate signaling required for mitotic exit and cytokinesis. In budding yeast, the Bub2-Bfa1 complex keeps Tem1 inactive until the spindle is properly oriented, thus inhibiting MEN activation.\" [PMID:16449187, PMID:22525225]\n+synonym: \"Bfa1-Bub2 complex\" NARROW []\n+synonym: \"Byr4-Cdc16 GAP complex\" NARROW []\n is_a: GO:1902773 ! GTPase activator complex\n relationship: part_of GO:0005816 ! spindle pole body\n+property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31636\" xsd:anyURI\n created_by: bhm\n creation_date: 2014-03-17T14:34:21Z\n-\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,16 @@\n+## Issue #31636: GO:1990334 rename\n+\n+- No dedicated DOSDP appears necessary for this edit.\n+- This is an existing cellular component protein complex term with no logical definition.\n+- Precedent in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo` supports species-agnostic umbrella labels for conserved SIN/MEN complexes, especially `GO:0160065` `SIN/MEN signaling complex`.\n+- For this issue, the design choice is:\n+  - keep the existing asserted parent and relationships unchanged\n+  - avoid adding `intersection_of` axioms\n+  - use a broader, pan-species label for the main term\n+  - retain species-specific legacy names as `NARROW` synonyms\n+\n+Relevant precedent:\n+\n+- `GO:0160065` `SIN/MEN signaling complex`\n+- `GO:1990811` `MWP complex` with founding-species synonym retained as `EXACT`\n+- `GO:1990879` `CST complex` with species-specific complexes retained as `NARROW`\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,15 @@\n+## PMID:16449187 \"Disappearance of the budding yeast Bub2-Bfa1 complex from the mother-bound spindle pole contributes to mitotic exit\"\n+\n+Primary experimental support for the existing Saccharomyces example. Confirms that Bub2 and Bfa1 function together as a two-component GAP regulating Tem1 and mitotic exit.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:16449187 \"Budding yeast spindle position checkpoint is engaged by misoriented spindles and prevents mitotic exit by inhibiting the G protein Tem1 through the GTPase-activating protein (GAP) Bub2/Bfa1.\"\n+    - Bub2/Bfa1 is explicitly described as the GAP acting on Tem1.\n+    - This supports retaining the budding-yeast complex name as a narrow synonym and as the organism-specific example in the definition.\n+\n+## PMID:22525225 \"Hippo signalling in the G2/M cell cycle phase: lessons learned from the yeast MEN and SIN pathways\"\n+\n+Review-level support that MEN in budding yeast and SIN in fission yeast are cognate signaling systems, justifying a species-agnostic umbrella label spanning both networks.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:22525225 \"All members of the Hippo core signalling cassette are conserved from yeast to humans, whereby the yeast analogues of Hippo, Mats and Lats are central components of the mitotic exit network and septation initiation network in budding and fission yeast, respectively.\"\n+    - Supports treating MEN and SIN as corresponding conserved yeast signaling systems.\n+    - Justifies broadening the primary term label from the budding-yeast-specific `Bfa1-Bub2 complex` to `SIN/MEN two-component GAP complex`.\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_1990334.obo","relativePath":"terms/GO_1990334.obo","type":"update","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_1990334.obo\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_1990334.obo\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/terms/GO_1990334.obo\n@@ -1,10 +1,12 @@\n [Term]\n id: GO:1990334\n-name: Bfa1-Bub2 complex\n+name: SIN/MEN two-component GAP complex\n namespace: cellular_component\n-def: \"A protein complex that acts as a two-component GTPase-activating protein for Tem1 GTPase, thus regulating a signal transduction cascade, called the mitotic exit network (MEN), which is required for mitotic exit and cytokinesis. Bub2/Bfa1 keeps Tem1 inactive until the spindle is properly oriented, thus inhibiting MEN activation.\" [GOC:bhm, PMID:16449187]\n+def: \"A protein complex that acts as a two-component GTPase-activating protein in the septation initiation network (SIN) or mitotic exit network (MEN), thereby helping regulate signaling required for mitotic exit and cytokinesis. In budding yeast, the Bub2-Bfa1 complex keeps Tem1 inactive until the spindle is properly oriented, thus inhibiting MEN activation.\" [PMID:16449187, PMID:22525225]\n+synonym: \"Bfa1-Bub2 complex\" NARROW []\n+synonym: \"Byr4-Cdc16 GAP complex\" NARROW []\n is_a: GO:1902773 ! GTPase activator complex\n relationship: part_of GO:0005816 ! spindle pole body\n+property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31636\" xsd:anyURI\n created_by: bhm\n creation_date: 2014-03-17T14:34:21Z\n-\n","additions":5,"deletions":3},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","relativePath":"DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,16 @@\n+## Issue #31636: GO:1990334 rename\n+\n+- No dedicated DOSDP appears necessary for this edit.\n+- This is an existing cellular component protein complex term with no logical definition.\n+- Precedent in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo` supports species-agnostic umbrella labels for conserved SIN/MEN complexes, especially `GO:0160065` `SIN/MEN signaling complex`.\n+- For this issue, the design choice is:\n+  - keep the existing asserted parent and relationships unchanged\n+  - avoid adding `intersection_of` axioms\n+  - use a broader, pan-species label for the main term\n+  - retain species-specific legacy names as `NARROW` synonyms\n+\n+Relevant precedent:\n+\n+- `GO:0160065` `SIN/MEN signaling complex`\n+- `GO:1990811` `MWP complex` with founding-species synonym retained as `EXACT`\n+- `GO:1990879` `CST complex` with species-specific complexes retained as `NARROW`\n","additions":16,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md","relativePath":"RESEARCH