{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778991655508,"sessionID":"ses_1cbe49a24ffeMllnW9kPHlNnLD","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_gALxdHwU8RajXDU5bphYyG7i","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Updated GO:1990334 as requested.\n+\n+- Renamed the primary label to `SIN/MEN two-component GAP complex` to make the term species-agnostic.\n+- Retained `Bfa1-Bub2 complex` and added `Byr4-Cdc16 GAP complex` as `NARROW` synonyms.\n+- Revised the definition to cover both MEN and SIN, while keeping the budding-yeast Tem1 example.\n+\n+Changes committed locally and ready for PR #<NN>.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+Updated `GO:1990334` to remove the budding-yeast-specific primary label while preserving species-specific names as narrower synonyms.\n+\n+Summary of changes:\n+\n+- Renamed `GO:1990334` from `Bfa1-Bub2 complex` to `SIN/MEN two-component GAP complex`.\n+- Added narrow synonyms:\n+  - `Bfa1-Bub2 complex`\n+  - `Byr4-Cdc16 GAP complex`\n+- Revised the definition so the main text is species-agnostic across the septation initiation network (SIN) and mitotic exit network (MEN), while retaining the budding-yeast `Tem1` example explicitly.\n+- Added `term_tracker_item` metadata for issue `#31636`.\n+- Left the asserted parent and location unchanged:\n+  - `is_a: GO:1902773 ! GTPase activator complex`\n+  - `relationship: part_of GO:0005816 ! spindle pole body`\n+\n+Rationale:\n+\n+- The issue requested a species-agnostic rename.\n+- Existing ontology precedent already uses umbrella `SIN/MEN` terminology, notably `GO:0160065` `SIN/MEN signaling complex`.\n+- `PMID:16449187` supports the budding-yeast Bub2-Bfa1 complex as a two-component GAP acting on Tem1.\n+- `PMID:22525225` supports treating MEN and SIN as corresponding conserved yeast signaling systems, which justifies the broader primary label.\n+\n+Validation and checks completed:\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: issue reviewed and scope defined\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed before edits\n+- [x] RESEARCH: literature checked and summarized in `RESEARCH.md` (not committed)\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: checked current term and related SIN/MEN complex precedent with `obo-grep.pl`\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: reviewed precedent and documented in `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md` (not committed)\n+- [x] EDITS: used `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl` workflow\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: no logical axioms added; existing classification preserved\n+- [x] METADATA: added `term_tracker_item`; did not alter `created_by` / `creation_date` on existing term\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed after edits\n+- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: supporting text in `RESEARCH.md` validated with `linkml-reference-validator`\n+\n+Files committed:\n+\n+- `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,7 @@\n+Updated GO:1990334 as requested.\n+\n+- Renamed the primary label to `SIN/MEN two-component GAP complex` to make the term species-agnostic.\n+- Retained `Bfa1-Bub2 complex` and added `Byr4-Cdc16 GAP complex` as `NARROW` synonyms.\n+- Revised the definition to cover both MEN and SIN, while keeping the budding-yeast Tem1 example.\n+\n+Changes committed locally and ready for PR #<NN>.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@\n+Updated `GO:1990334` to remove the budding-yeast-specific primary label while preserving species-specific names as narrower synonyms.\n+\n+Summary of changes:\n+\n+- Renamed `GO:1990334` from `Bfa1-Bub2 complex` to `SIN/MEN two-component GAP complex`.\n+- Added narrow synonyms:\n+  - `Bfa1-Bub2 complex`\n+  - `Byr4-Cdc16 GAP complex`\n+- Revised the definition so the main text is species-agnostic across the septation initiation network (SIN) and mitotic exit network (MEN), while retaining the budding-yeast `Tem1` example explicitly.\n+- Added `term_tracker_item` metadata for issue `#31636`.\n+- Left the asserted parent and location unchanged:\n+  - `is_a: GO:1902773 ! GTPase activator complex`\n+  - `relationship: part_of GO:0005816 ! spindle pole body`\n+\n+Rationale:\n+\n+- The issue requested a species-agnostic rename.\n+- Existing ontology precedent already uses umbrella `SIN/MEN` terminology, notably `GO:0160065` `SIN/MEN signaling complex`.\n+- `PMID:16449187` supports the budding-yeast Bub2-Bfa1 complex as a two-component GAP acting on Tem1.\n+- `PMID:22525225` supports treating MEN and SIN as corresponding conserved yeast signaling systems, which justifies the broader primary label.\n+\n+Validation and checks completed:\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: issue reviewed and scope defined\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed before edits\n+- [x] RESEARCH: literature checked and summarized in `RESEARCH.md` (not committed)\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: checked current term and related SIN/MEN complex precedent with `obo-grep.pl`\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: reviewed precedent and documented in `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md` (not committed)\n+- [x] EDITS: used `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl` workflow\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: no logical axioms added; existing classification preserved\n+- [x] METADATA: added `term_tracker_item`; did not alter `created_by` / `creation_date` on existing term\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed after edits\n+- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: supporting text in `RESEARCH.md` validated with `linkml-reference-validator`\n+\n+Files committed:\n+\n+- `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","relativePath":"ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,7 @@\n+Updated GO:1990334 as requested.\n+\n+- Renamed the primary label to `SIN/MEN two-component GAP complex` to make the term species-agnostic.\n+- Retained `Bfa1-Bub2 complex` and added `Byr4-Cdc16 GAP complex` as `NARROW` synonyms.\n+- Revised the definition to cover both MEN and SIN, while keeping the budding-yeast Tem1 example.\n+\n+Changes committed locally and ready for PR #<NN>.\n","additions":7,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md","relativePath":"PR_COMMENTS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@\n+Updated `GO:1990334` to remove the budding-yeast-specific primary label while preserving species-specific names as narrower synonyms.\n+\n+Summary of changes:\n+\n+- Renamed `GO:1990334` from `Bfa1-Bub2 complex` to `SIN/MEN two-component GAP complex`.\n+- Added narrow synonyms:\n+  - `Bfa1-Bub2 complex`\n+  - `Byr4-Cdc16 GAP complex`\n+- Revised the definition so the main text is species-agnostic across the septation initiation network (SIN) and mitotic exit network (MEN), while retaining the budding-yeast `Tem1` example explicitly.\n+- Added `term_tracker_item` metadata for issue `#31636`.\n+- Left the asserted parent and location unchanged:\n+  - `is_a: GO:1902773 ! GTPase activator complex`\n+  - `relationship: part_of GO:0005816 ! spindle pole body`\n+\n+Rationale:\n+\n+- The issue requested a species-agnostic rename.\n+- Existing ontology precedent already uses umbrella `SIN/MEN` terminology, notably `GO:0160065` `SIN/MEN signaling complex`.\n+- `PMID:16449187` supports the budding-yeast Bub2-Bfa1 complex as a two-component GAP acting on Tem1.\n+- `PMID:22525225` supports treating MEN and SIN as corresponding conserved yeast signaling systems, which justifies the broader primary label.\n+\n+Validation and checks completed:\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: issue reviewed and scope defined\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed before edits\n+- [x] RESEARCH: literature checked and summarized in `RESEARCH.md` (not committed)\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: checked current term and related SIN/MEN complex precedent with `obo-grep.pl`\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: reviewed precedent and documented in `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md` (not committed)\n+- [x] EDITS: used `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl` workflow\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: no logical axioms added; existing classification preserved\n+- [x] METADATA: added `term_tracker_item`; did not alter `created_by` / `creation_date` on existing term\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed after edits\n+- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: supporting text in `RESEARCH.md` validated with `linkml-reference-validator`\n+\n+Files committed:\n+\n+- `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n","additions":37,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","time":{"start":1778991655493,"end":1778991655505}},"id":"prt_e342a34da001Cs5xjrAwHtxERD","sessionID":"ses_1cbe49a24ffeMllnW9kPHlNnLD","messageID":"msg_e342a2d43001po4D84sDokgHc4"}}
